{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"5f7c4bd9-c618-474b-89cd-edd80678c214","agentId":"aa3b0c761792d8a1a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"## Source Extractor\n\nResearch question: \"Competitive landscape and market analysis for AI-powered recruitment platforms targeting solo/independent recruiters and small recruiting agencies (teams of 5-10), with a freemium model (free individual tier + paid team tier).\n\nResearch these dimensions specifically:\n1. Existing recruitment platforms (ATS, recruiting CRM, applicant tracking) that target solo recruiters and small agencies — e.g. Recruit CRM, Loxo, Crelate, Manatal, JobAdder, Zoho Recruit, Bullhorn, RecruiterFlow, Vincere, iSmartRecruit, Ceipal, Tracker, Hireflow, hiring tools like Workable, Ashby, Greenhouse (note which are NOT for small/solo). For each relevant one: target customer, pricing/tiers, free tier availability, AI features, key strengths/weaknesses.\n2. Which of these use a freemium or free-tier model (Zoho Recruit free plan, etc.) and how they monetize. How \"easy to start\" / self-serve onboarding is positioned.\n3. Where AI is being applied in recruiting today (resume parsing, candidate matching/ranking, sourcing, outreach email generation, interview scheduling, candidate Q&A, job description writing, chrome extensions for sourcing from LinkedIn). Which features are table-stakes vs differentiators in 2025-2026.\n4. The pain points of small/independent recruiters: data scattered across WhatsApp/Excel/Google Drive, time spent on admin, lack of context on past placements, no revenue visibility. What tools claim to solve these and gaps that remain.\n5. Pricing benchmarks: typical per-seat/month pricing for recruiting CRM/ATS at the small-agency level, and what free tiers include.\n6. Market size and trends for recruitment software / recruiting CRM, especially the SMB / independent recruiter segment.\"\n\nFetch and extract key claims from this source:\n**URL:** https://recruitersforge.com/recruit-crm-vs-manatal-vs-loxo/\n**Title:** Recruit CRM vs Manatal vs Loxo - The Ultimate 3-Way Comparison (2026)\n**Found via:** AI features table-stakes vs differentiator search\n\n## Task\n1. Use WebFetch to retrieve the page content.\n2. Assess source quality: primary research/institution? secondary reporting? blog/opinion? forum? unreliable?\n3. Extract 2-5 FALSIFIABLE claims that bear on the research question. Each claim must:\n   - be a concrete, checkable statement (not vague generalities)\n   - include a direct quote from the source as support\n   - be rated central/supporting/tangential to the research question\n4. Note publish date if available.\n\nIf the fetch fails or the page is irrelevant/paywalled, return claims: [] and sourceQuality: \"unreliable\".\n\nStructured output only."},"uuid":"d889061b-f196-4647-ba9b-208eff7a1db2","timestamp":"2026-06-16T10:20:11.052Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"/Users/ashwin","sessionId":"4e28c02b-de8f-44d8-9fbb-ee619bc310ea","version":"2.1.167","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
